{
  "topic_order": 2,
  "module_type": "learning",
  "exercise_title": "Unit 2: Modal Verbs (Tables)",
  "activities": [
    {
      "type": "Học Từ Vựng (Vocabulary)",
      "content": {
        "word": "1. May - Must - Can't",
        "meaning": "<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; text-align: left;\"><tr style=\"background:#f1f5f9;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; font-weight: bold; width: 25%; color: #0f172a;\">May<br>Must<br>Can't</td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; color: #334155;\">(= perhaps)<br>(= I think, I suppose)<br>(= I don't think, I don't suppose)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; color: #1e293b;\">She <b>must</b> be at work.<br>She <b>can't</b> be at home.<br>She <b>may</b> have gone out.</td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; color: #1e293b;\">I <b>think</b> she is at work.<br>I <b>don't think</b> she is at home.<br><b>Perhaps</b> she went out.</td></tr></table>"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Học Từ Vựng (Vocabulary)",
      "content": {
        "word": "2. Must - Can't - May + Infinitive",
        "meaning": "<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; text-align: left;\"><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Simple Present<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">Perhaps he <b>works</b> as a teacher.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He may <b>work</b> as a teacher.</i></td></tr><tr style=\"background:#f8fafc;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Future<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">I don't think he <b>will win</b>.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He can't <b>win</b>.</i></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Continuous<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">I suppose he <b>is working</b> hard.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Continuous Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He must <b>be working</b> hard.</i></td></tr><tr style=\"background:#f8fafc;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Future Continuous<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">Perhaps they <b>will be playing</b> tennis.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Continuous Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">They may <b>be playing</b> tennis.</i></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Simple Past<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">I don't think he <b>worked</b> very hard.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Perfect Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He can't <b>have worked</b> very hard.</i></td></tr><tr style=\"background:#f8fafc;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Present Perfect<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">Perhaps he <b>has left</b> work.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Perfect Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He may <b>have left</b> work.</i></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Past Continuous<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">I don't believe she <b>was working</b> last week.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Perfect Continuous Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">She can't <b>have been working</b> last week.</i></td></tr><tr style=\"background:#f8fafc;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Perfect Continuous<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">I think they <b>have been living</b> here a long time.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\">Perfect Continuous Infinitive<br><i style=\"color:#475569;\">They must <b>have been living</b> here a long time.</i></td></tr></table>"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Học Từ Vựng (Vocabulary)",
      "content": {
        "word": "3. Mustn't - Needn't",
        "meaning": "<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; text-align: left;\"><tr style=\"background:#f1f5f9;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; color: #0f172a;\">Mustn't <span style=\"font-weight:normal; color:#475569;\">(= it's forbidden / not allowed)</span></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; font-weight: bold; color: #0f172a;\">Needn't <span style=\"font-weight:normal; color:#475569;\">(= it's not necessary)</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\"><i style=\"color:#1e293b;\">You <b>mustn't</b> smoke in hospitals.<br>You <b>are not allowed</b> to smoke in hospitals.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\"><i style=\"color:#1e293b;\">You <b>needn't</b> learn it by heart.<br>It's <b>not necessary</b> for you to learn it by heart.</i></td></tr></table>"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Học Từ Vựng (Vocabulary)",
      "content": {
        "word": "4. Didn't Need to - Needn't Have",
        "meaning": "<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; text-align: left;\"><tr style=\"background:#f1f5f9;\"><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; color: #1e293b; line-height: 1.6;\"><b>Didn't need to</b> shows that it wasn't necessary for something to happen and it <b style=\"color:#dc2626;\">didn't happen</b>.<br><b>Needn't have</b> shows that it wasn't necessary for something to happen but it <b style=\"color:#16a34a;\">did happen</b>.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; width: 50%;\"><i style=\"color:#475569;\">He <b>didn't need to</b> go to work on Sunday.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; width: 50%;\"><i style=\"color:#475569;\">It wasn't necessary for him to go to work because it was Sunday.</i></td></tr><tr style=\"background:#f8fafc;\"><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\"><i style=\"color:#475569;\">She <b>needn't have bought</b> so many eggs.</i></td><td style=\"padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;\"><i style=\"color:#475569;\">It wasn't necessary for her to buy as many eggs as she did.</i></td></tr></table>"
      }
    }
  ]
}